# Documentation Rules

## File Placement
- All `.md` files go in `docs/` — **no exceptions except `README.md`** at the project root
- Never create markdown files (guides, references, quickstarts, etc.) in the root directory

## File Naming
- Use uppercase with underscores: `LAMBDA_FUNCTIONS.md`, `FEATURE_NAME.md`

## Every Feature Gets a Doc
Every new feature must have a README in `docs/` covering:
- What it does, how it works, how to use it, key implementation details

## Lambda Documentation
Every new Lambda handler must be added to `docs/LAMBDA_FUNCTIONS.md`.

## Documentation Reference Table
Every new `docs/*.md` file must be added to the reference table in the root `README.md`:

```markdown
## Documentation

| Document | Description |
|----------|-------------|
| [Lambda Functions](docs/LAMBDA_FUNCTIONS.md) | All Lambda handlers, triggers, and config |
| [Feature Name](docs/FEATURE_NAME.md) | Description of the feature |
```
